The chairman and chief executive of Dangote Group, Alhaji Aliko Dangote, has said yesterday in Kano that the main priority of the company was to provide job opportunities to teeming jobless Nigerians Dangote was represented by Alhaji Mansur Ahmed, at the Dangote Day at the ongoing Kano trade fair. According to  Ahmed, “Dangote had succeeded in impacting on the lives of every Nigerian by way of touching their lives positively through its numerous products such as Dangote Cement, salt, flour, Dono Maggi cubes, Semolina among others, adding that no one would wake up in his house without having anything to do with our products.” He said the company was currently making moves to ensure that it got a permanent spot at the trade fair complex for it to have something to call its own.